The last edition of The Review Show features performances from Hendra, Ben Watt's first solo album in over thirty years. Watch Ben and Bernard Butler performing The Levels. 
 In the programme, Martha Kearney and guests Professor Sarah Churchwell, Paul Morley and Sarfraz Manzoor discuss Harry Hill's X Factor-inspired musical, I Can't Sing; the UK premiere of the Tony Award-winning Urinetown; Richard Ayoade's film adaptation of Dostoyevsky's The Double; Designs of the Year at the Design Museum; BBC One's World War One drama The Crimson Field; and Richard King's book On Offence. 
 Watch the programme, including another track from Ben Watt and Bernard Butler, on BBC iPlayer until Saturday 5 April. It is also repeated on BBC Two, Thursday 17 April.
